## Analysis: memory_search Gemini embedding — hardcoded model name outdated

Simple fix. The Gemini embedding API deprecated `embedding-001` and now requires `text-embedding-004` (or `text-embedding-005` for newer accounts).

### Root cause

```ts
// Likely in src/memory/embedding-providers/gemini.ts or similar:
const model = 'models/embedding-001'; // ← deprecated, returns 404
```

### Fix

```ts
// Update the default model to the current supported version:
const model = options?.embeddingModel ?? 'models/text-embedding-004';
```

### Why this is a one-line fix

The Gemini Embedding API has been stable on `text-embedding-004` since early 2024. The only question is whether the config allows users to override the model name — if not, add an option to `providers.google` config:

```json
{
  "providers": {
    "google": {
      "embeddingModel": "text-embedding-004"
    }
  }
}
```

### Note for users on older accounts

Some Google AI Studio accounts still support `embedding-001`. To avoid breaking those, the fix should:
1. Default to `text-embedding-004`  
2. Allow override via config
3. Or detect the 404 and retry with `text-embedding-004` as fallback

The quick path: update the hardcoded string, done.
